title: For Sale:  Remington 597 .22LR W/ Threaded Heavy Barrel & Extras
postcontent: This Remington 597 was purchased new by me, and has less than 100 rds. fired through it.  It is equipped with a 16.5 inch heavy barrel, with a factory-threaded muzzle for mounting a suppressor or other device.   I've read online that this barrel has the preferred 5R rifling, but cannot yet confirm this information.  I do know that this particular model has not been available from Remington for several years.  I have installed a Volquartsen target hammer ($45) which results in a nice, light 1 3/4 lb. trigger pull (the original hammer is included in case a heavier 3.5 lb. pull is desired).   Also included is a Volquartsen Exact Edge extractor ($20, not yet installed), and and six additional 3rd generation 10 rd. factory magazines ($16 each).  The barrel has been free-floated from the synthetic green stock.  In the limited amount of rounds that I've fired through it, I found it to be as accurate as my bolt-action rifles.  I just don't shoot it enough to justify keeping it.  My selling price is $400, with a trade value of $450.  I may be interested in trading for full-size 9mm CZ or Browning High Power pistols, or "tactical" (not hunting) rifles or shotguns, but would prefer to sell rather than trade, and will meet in N. Austin.  Shipping may be possible, at additional cost.  Thank you.For those unfamiliar with the 597, it is a much newer & more modern design than its main competitor, the Ruger 10/22 (1997 versus 1964).  The stock seems to be designed more for adults, with a more pronounced pistol grip.  The bolt rides smoother on two tool-steel guide rods (versus one on the Ruger), and there is a last shot bolt hold open feature.  The 597 is considered by many shooters to be more accurate out of the box than the 10/22.

title: For Sale:  Ithaca Grade 2E 28 Gauge - NID, BEAVERTAIL, SST 65% FACTORY COLOR, RARE!
postcontent:
Ithaca Grade 2E 28 Gauge SxS   NID, BEAVERTAIL, SST, 65% FACTORY COLOR, RARE!   General Specs: Ithaca, Year 1936, 28 Gauge, 5lb 15oz, Side-by-Side   Serial Number: 461325   For any serious shooter/collector, the small-bore Classic American Doubles are the pinnacle of desirability. They are few in numbers and high in cost. When it comes to the 28ga. only two of the Classic American double gun producers come into play; Parker and Ithaca. As most who seek these small bores are aware, the Parker guns are very costly in 28ga. as only a handful of them were produced. The Ithaca NID is an awesome gun with brilliant mechanics, super-strong receiver, and its affordable cost. This Ithaca NID Grade 2E, sn461325 made in 1936, is exceptionally rare as it is 1 of 58 total production of all Ithaca NID 28ga. Grade 2’s. Keep in mind there are likely less than 10 of the 58 that were produced with the ultra-desirable beavertail forend, Ithaca Single Selective trigger, and ejectors, SO THIS GUN IS VERY RARE INDEED! Even more importantly, the gun retains 65% vivid factory original case color, 98% factory blue, all factory original wood with a perfect oil finish, no cracks or repairs, clear sharp Grade 2 engraving, all in a 6lb. package with perfect mechanics. If you try and compare this gun to Parker’s Grade 2 gun, or GHE grade, the price of the Parker with these features and factory condition would cost twice as much as the Ithaca. Ithaca NID small bore guns represent the very best value in today’s shooter/collector market with relatively low cost that will surely increase the most in value during the next 5 years. The mechanics are perfect inside and out, bores are mirrors, no splits or cracks anywhere, excellent screws, barrels are tight on breech face and hinge pin with lever well right of center.
